{"build_type":"library","description":"read_entire_file_into_string: read a whole file at path into a NUL-terminated string. FAIL-HARD per coding-law: never returns NULL and never writes out of bounds. On any failure it returns an empty string so callers parse it safely (decode_entire_source_building_document of empty yields NULL and the caller's existing zero-branch fires) instead of segfaulting. Failure cases: open<0; fstat<0; the path is NOT a regular file (S_ISREG) — directories are rejected here because lseek(SEEK_END) on a directory returns INT64_MAX and size+1 would overflow the arena allocator; lseek size<0; allocation failure; read<0.","module_name":"retrieve-entire-document-inside-string","package_name":"retrieve-entire-document-inside-string","function_definitions":{"retrieve-entire-document-inside-string":{"return_type":"str","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"path","parameter_type":"str"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"seek_end","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c_statsize","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":160},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c_ifmt","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":61440},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"c_ifreg","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":32768},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","